Install Ubuntu 18.04. Always use UEFI when avalible. Create efi partition (~650 MB), create root partition and mount it on / (~500 GB, or at least 300 GB), create SWAP (optional, twice as big as RAM).

If laptop, install WIFI drivers. Check rltwifi_new (Realtek drivers) git clone https://github.com/lwfinger/rtlwifi_new.git

Update the system:
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade

Install utilities for compiling from source:
sudo apt install linux-headers-generic build-essential git

Install tweaks:
sudo apt install gnome-tweak-tool

Install Gnome extensions: AlternateTab, Caffeine, Clipboard Indicatior, Drop Down Terminal, Impatience, Screenshot tool, Show desktop from overview, system-monitor, Top Panel Workspace Scroll:
sudo apt install chrome-gnome-shell



Change the Ubuntu left bar for the traditional Gnome left bar.


